import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom'; export default function RenderSignUp () { const Navigate = useNavigate(); async function signup () { // sends username, password from input server then creates s3 bucket in username and stores details on mongo const username = document.getElementById('signupusername').value;// get username password and email const password = document.getElementById('signuppass').value; const email = document.getElementById('signupemail').value; let signupdata = { Username: username, Password: password, Email: email } let options = { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', }, body: JSON.stringify(signupdata), } let signinurl = 'http://192.168.1.93:4001/signup/' + username let response = await fetch(signinurl, options) let convert = await response.json () console.log("User signup completed created document is:") console.log(convert) if ( response.status === 401 || response.status === 400){// handle not a match alert("Your usernam") // Navigate("/signIn") return false } else if ( response.status === 200){ // if password is a match return auth'd username alert("user found chkauth returning user") console.log("authorized by api", convert.AuthdUser) return convert.AuthdUser } Navigate("/") } return( <> Sign Up
